    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Thelypteris afzelii improperly include inducing vomiting, experiencing nausea, triggering allergic reactions, and triggering diarrhea. These side effects are likely due to the presence of toxic compounds such as polyacetylenes and terpenoids, which can be released when the plant is ingested or when its extracts come into contact with the skin. When ingested, these compounds can cause gastrointestinal distress, including vomiting and diarrhea, and may also trigger allergic reactions in sensitive individuals. In some cases, exposure to Thelypteris afzelii extracts may also cause nausea and vomiting due to the irritation of the gastrointestinal tract. The severity of these side effects can vary depending on the individual's sensitivity and the amount of the plant or its extracts that is ingested or applied.",
    "uses": "Thelypteris afzelii is not a well-studied species, but its leaves have been used in traditional medicine for various purposes. They are believed to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. The plant has been used to treat fever, cough, and respiratory issues. Additionally, the leaves are said to have antioxidant properties that may help protect against oxidative stress. However, further research is needed to confirm the efficacy and safety of using Thelypteris afzelii for medicinal purposes.",
    "taxonomy": "Thelypteris afzelii is classified under the family Thelypteridaceae. It belongs to the order Polypodiales and the class Polypodiopsida. This plant is also known as a type of fern and is further classified as a member of the genus Thelypteris. Thelypteris afzelii is native to tropical regions and is often found in areas with high humidity and moderate temperatures. Its classification reflects its unique characteristics and evolutionary history as a member of the fern family.",
    "benefits": "Thelypteris afzelii is traditionally used in various cultures for its medicinal properties. The plant is believed to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects, which may help to reduce stress and promote overall well-being. It is also thought to have antimicrobial properties, which could aid in the treatment of certain infections. The plant's leaves have been used in traditional medicine to treat various health issues, including fever, cough, and digestive problems. Further research is needed to confirm the effectiveness of Thelypteris afzelii for these potential health benefits.",
    "parts": "Thelypteris afzelii. The plant Thelypteris afzelii is said to have potential medicinal properties. The leaves of Thelypteris afzelii are reportedly used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments. Research suggests that the plant may possess antibacterial, antifungal, and anti-inflammatory properties. Further studies are needed to confirm the effectiveness of Thelypteris afzelii in treating specific medical conditions.",
    "intro": "Thelypteris afzelii, also known as the African maiden fern, is a species of fern that belongs to the family Thelypteridaceae. The health benefits of Thelypteris afzelii include its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties, which have been traditionally used to treat various ailments such as fever, rheumatism, and skin conditions. The bioactive constituents of this plant include flavonoids, alkaloids, and saponins, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. The most common herbal preparations made with Thelypteris afzelii include teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are used to support immune function, reduce inflammation, and promote overall well-being."
